Here is an example Python code to get the values of 'vinci' with its above key from the given list:

```
data = [
    {
        "case": { "customer_name": "string" },
        "Leads": { "customer_name": "also vinci in lead" },
        "RebateRecord": { "borrower_name": "vinci" }
    },
    {
        "case": { "customer_name": "vinci" },
        "Leads": { "customer_name": "string" },
        "RebateRecord": { "borrower_name": "vinci" }
    }
]

vinci_data = {}

for item in data:
    for key, value in item.items():
        if value.get("customer_name") == "vinci":
            vinci_data[key] = "vinci"

print(vinci_data)
```

